Author: mrlynch#5735
Content: there is a difference between privacy and anonymity, however in the digital age we live in you can't really have one without the other. nowadays having privacy is no longer enough.

Author: mrlynch#5735
Content: and i defer you to the work of cambridge analytica - even if you were pseudonymous (somewhat private) a profile could still be built based on your connections (friends, photos, etc.) - the same can not be achieved if you are anonymous and therefore your private life remains private
